  "datePublished": "2026-04-29",
  "description": "A morphism class in the predicate category, given by a sub-support inclusion dom(q) ↪ dom(p) between predicates. Encodes the relation 'q is a sub-predicate of p': q's cells are a structurally designated subset of p's cells, with q's values inherited from p's on that subset and extended by ⊥ outside. One of the four canonical generators of the predicate category.",
  "name": "Predicate specialization",
